  "market_context": "YM opens high creating the high of day from a daily key level (range high), breaking higher time frame SMT across the indices triad (NQ/ES/YM). Setup for a bearish day with a top-down expansion target toward the opposing range low.",
  "key_observation": "The daily range high broke HTF SMT, then the 4-hour formed a C2 closure (London reversal) creating a precision swing point and second-stage cracking correlation — the highest probability reversal confirmation with key level + two-stage PSP.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily, identified YM opening high from a key level forming the range high and breaking the higher time frame SMT across the indices triad.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to the 4-hour and observed a C2 closure (London reversal) which also created a precision swing point — the second-stage cracking correlation paired with the first-stage SMT at the range high (strength switch PSP).",
    "Step 3: Skipped the London entry; planned a New York continuation around 9:30 and dropped to the 30-minute to monitor structure.",
    "Step 4: On the 30-minute, observed 9:30 trading back into the range and sweeping a prior swing high, creating a first-stage SMT and a two-stage PSP at the key level.",
    "Step 5: Dropped to the 3-minute and entered on the change in state of delivery (order block confirmation) as a C2 reversal with a small wick.",
    "Step 6: Targeted the opposing side of the range (range low) as the higher time frame draw on liquidity — order-pairing ranges."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade executed on 3-minute CSD entry; price reached the targeted draw on liquidity (range low) over a roughly 7-hour duration — winning trade.",
  "lessons": "Top-down alignment from daily key level through 4H C2 closure, 30m two-stage PSP, and 3m CSD entry produces the highest probability reversal — pairing SMT with a key level followed by a two-stage PSP confirms expansion toward the opposing range extreme.",
